   The program under test ran the following command:
   ```
   /work/build/bin/exiv2 '-Mset Exif.CanonCs.LensType 124' '-Mset Exif.CanonCs.Lens 65 65 1' '-Mset Exif.CanonCs.MaxAperture 95' /work/test/data/template.exv
   ```
   The bug manifested when the program attempted to set the Exif tag value to
   95, which falls outside the valid range for the Exif tag CanonCs.
   
   Based on the code and the command line, it is clear that the root cause of
   the bug is the attempt to set the Exif tag value outside its valid range.
   
   The minimal local fix is to restrict the range of values that can be set for
   the Exif tag. For example, in the CanonCs class definition, you could add the
   following code:
   ```cpp
   class CanonCs {
       //...
       int maxAperture = 90; // restrict the maximum aperture value
       //...
   };
   ```
   However, a more thorough root-cause fix would be to add validation for the
   Exif tag values before attempting to set them. This could be done in the Exif
   class by adding the following code:
   ```cpp
   class Exif {
       //...
       void setTag(const std::string& tagName, const std::string& value) {
           if (tagName == "CanonCs") {
               int val = std::stoi(value);
               if (val < 65 || val > 90) {
                   throw std::invalid_argument("Invalid value for Exif tag CanonCs");
               }
           }
           //...
       }
       //...
   };
   ```
   This code checks if the tag name is "CanonCs" and if the value is within the
   valid range before attempting to set the tag.
   
   ```cpp
   </function>
   ##### Recommendation
   Fix the code by adding validation for the Exif tag values. For example, in the Exif class, add the following code:
   
   ```cpp
   class Exif {
       //...
       void setTag(const std::string& tagName, const std::string& value) {
           if (tagName == "CanonCs") {
               int val = std::stoi(value);
               if (val < 65 || val > 90) {
                   throw std::invalid_argument("Invalid value for Exif tag
   CanonCs");
               }
           }
           //...
       }
       //...
   };
   ```
   This will prevent attempts to set the Exif tag value outside its valid range and will throw an exception if an invalid value is provided.
